Ibidun Ighodalo, the wife of the senior pastor of Trinity House Church, Lagos, Ituah Ighodalo, is dead. In a statement by Asue Ighodalo, the families requested for privacy while mourning the late beauty queen. “The Ighodalo and Olaleye Ajayi families are deeply saddened to announce the sudden loss of our beloved wife and daughter Mrs. Ibidunni Ituah-Ighodalo who passed away in the early hours of today,” the statement read. “As you will understand, this is a difficult time for our families, and we will appreciate some privacy during this time. All information of burial proceedings will be provided in due course.” The 39-year-old reportedly suffered a cardiac arrest in the early hours of Sunday in Port Harcourt, Rivers State. Ibidun was working in Bayelsa and Rivers States, helping with the building of isolation centres for COVID-19 patients.